<h2>Write a New Post</h2>

<p>You can create a new post in two ways:</p>

<h3>1) Quick via GitHub</h3>
<p>
  <a class="btn btn-primary" href="https://github.com/{{ site.repo.owner }}/{{ site.repo.name }}/new/{{ site.repo.branch | default('main') }}?filename=src/posts/new-post.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Create new post on GitHub</a>
</p>
<p>This opens GitHub’s editor at <code>src/posts/new-post.md</code>. Paste this template:</p>
<pre><code>---
title: Your Post Title
description: One-line summary for lists and RSS.
date: {{ "now" | date }}
tags: [general]
layout: layouts/post.njk
cover: /assets/cover-abstract-1.svg
---

Write your content here in Markdown.
</code></pre>

<h3>2) Local CLI (fastest)</h3>
<p>From your local repo:</p>
<pre><code>npm run new -- --title "My New Post" --tags tech,notes --cover /assets/cover-abstract-1.svg</code></pre>
<p>This creates a new Markdown file in <code>src/posts/</code> with correct front matter and a slug.</p>

<h2>Editing Existing Posts</h2>
<p>Open any post and click “Edit on GitHub” near the bottom.</p>

